  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">Snapshots</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal">EmulatR can capture and restore full machine state to <text styleclass="Code Example">.axpsnap</text> files, so a long cold boot need only be paid once. Snapshot behavior is controlled by the <text styleclass="Code Example">EMULATR_*</text> environment variables and the matching <text styleclass="Code Example">--snapshot</text> / <text styleclass="Code Example">--autosnapshot</text> CLI flags.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading2">In this section</para>
    <para styleclass="NotesBox">-Snapshot Operations -- automatic saves, creating, restoring, and pruning.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="SeeAlso">See Also.</text></para>
